@TargetRenegade @Ironeagle21 The most amazing video game creation born from limitations will to me always be the Shadow Prince from the original Prince of Persia.
I saw an interview about it a while ago where one of the creators explained that they wanted to have another enemy or challenge to round out the game, but they did not have room to add another sprite to the game, so what they eventually came up with was using a trick to basically show a photo-negative version of the prince's sprite and used that as an entirely new enemy despite it actually being, "behind the scenes", the exact same sprite as the player character. And it was both great for antagonizing the player (since he had all the same animations as the Prince he could interact with things in the same way without them needing to actually add any more animations, doing stuff like closing doors to force you to go the long way around and, at one point, even stealing a health potion before you can get to it) and also had a really interesting boss fight once you finally caught him.

And they did all of that by essentially changing a 1 to a -1 when displaying the sprite, because they literally just didn't have the disk space to add anything more than that.
